{"bill":{"bill_id":1641893,"change_hash":"8a5bd3f7c08abe8c7db50b440375eb10","session_id":1988,"session":{"session_id":1988,"state_id":46,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/VA\/bill\/HB1501\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/lis.virginia.gov\/cgi-bin\/legp604.exe?231+sum+HB1501","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-01-25","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-03","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-03","event":9},{"date":"2023-01-20","event":10},{"date":"2023-01-25","event":2},{"date":"2023-01-27","event":9}],"state":"VA","state_id":46,"bill_number":"HB1501","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"H","body_id":7,"current_body":"S","current_body_id":8,"title":"Law-enforcement civilian oversight bodies; requirements of members.","description":"Law-enforcement civilian oversight bodies; requirements. Law-enforcement civilian oversight bodies; requirements. Requires every member appointed to a locality's law-enforcement civilian oversight body to observe within 90 days of the member's appointment a law-enforcement officer employed with such locality's law-enforcement agency while such law-enforcement officer is engaged in his official duties and that such observation total no fewer than 24 hours, a portion of which includes a ride-along with a law-enforcement officer. The bill also provides that any disciplinary determination recommended by a law-enforcement civilian oversight body shall be advisory and that if any law-enforcement agency declines to implement such recommendation, such agency shall create and make available to the public within 30 days from the date such recommendation is reported to such agency a written public record of its rationale for declining to implement such recommendation. Finally, the bill requires each law-enforcement civilian oversight body to include at least one retired law-enforcement officer as a voting member; under current law, a retired law-enforcement officer may serve on such body as an advisory, nonvoting ex officio member.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-03","committee_id":4177,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Public Safety"},{"date":"2023-01-17","committee_id":4576,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Public Safety: Subcommittee #2"},{"date":"2023-01-27","committee_id":4165,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Judiciary"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-03","action":"Prefiled and ordered printed; offered 01\/11\/23 23100457D","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-03","action":"Referred to Committee on Public Safety","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-17","action":"Assigned PS sub: Subcommittee #2","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-19","action":"Subcommittee recommends reporting with amendments (5-Y 3-N)","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-20","action":"Reported from Public Safety with amendment(s) (12-Y 10-N)","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-24","action":"Read first time","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-25","action":"Read second time","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-25","action":"Committee amendment agreed to","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-25","action":"Engrossed by House as amended HB1501E","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-25","action":"Printed as engrossed 23100457D-E","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-26","action":"Read third time and passed House (51-Y 47-N)","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-26","action":"VOTE: Passage (51-Y 47-N)","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-27","action":"Constitutional reading dispensed","chamber":"S","chamber_id":